    "base_path":  "/guidance/electrification-of-heat-demonstration-project",
    "content_id":  "bd194feb-c540-4ee9-a72a-3beaa645a64e",
    "description":  "This project looks to demonstrate the feasibility of a large-scale roll-out of innovative heat pump systems in a representative range of British homes. ",
    "details":  {
                    "attachments":  [

                                    ],
                    "body":  "\u003cdiv class=\"govspeak\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe Electrification of Heat Demonstration Project aims to demonstrate the feasibility of a large-scale roll-out of heat pumps in Great Britain by installing innovative heat pumps in a representative range of 750 homes, together with new products and services designed to overcome some of the barriers to deployment.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"project-objectives\"\u003eProject objectives\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe project objectives are to:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003edevelop, test and evaluate innovative products and services that increase the appeal of heat pumps and identify optimal solutions for a wide range of homes\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003edemonstrate that heat pumps, including gas-electric hybrids, can deliver high consumer satisfaction across a wide range of consumers in Great Britain\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003edemonstrate the practical and technical feasibility of heat pumps, including gas-electric hybrids, across Great Britain’s diverse housing stock\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003ecapture learning from the project to help improve awareness across the heating supply chain, raise acceptance and support wider deployment of heat pumps in Great Britain\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"project-delivery\"\u003eProject delivery\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eApproximately £14.6 million has been made available as part of the \u003cabbr title=\"Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy\"\u003eBEIS\u003c/abbr\u003e Energy Innovation Programme’s Electrification of Heat Demonstration Project.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe project will install and monitor 750 innovative heat pump systems across a representative range of housing archetypes, with the majority on the gas grid.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eTo achieve this, \u003cabbr title=\"Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy\"\u003eBEIS\u003c/abbr\u003e has appointed:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003ea management contractor to manage and coordinate the project on behalf of \u003cabbr title=\"Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy\"\u003eBEIS\u003c/abbr\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003e3 regional delivery contractors to deliver the project\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003ean independent evaluation contractor to evaluate the overall delivery of the project against the agreed performance indicators and metrics\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"management-contractor\"\u003eManagement contractor\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn November 2019, a consortium led by Energy Systems Catapult with Delta Energy and Environment and Oxford Computer Consultants was awarded the Management Contract for the Electrification of Heat Demonstration Project.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"delivery-contractors\"\u003eDelivery contractors\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA competition to appoint 3 delivery contractors concluded in June 2020. The appointed delivery contractors are:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eE.ON who will undertake the trial in Newcastle\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eOVO Energy who will undertake the trial in the South East of England\u003c/li\u003e\n  \u003cli\u003eWarmworks who will undertake the trial in the South East of Scotland\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eMore details about the 3 delivery contractors can be found on the \u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://gov.uk/government/publications/electrification-of-heat-demonstration-project-successful-bids\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003esuccessful bids page\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"evaluation-contractor\"\u003eEvaluation contractor\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn March 2020 ICF Consulting Services Limited was awarded the Evaluation Contract for the Electrification of Heat Demonstration Project.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"apply-to-participate\"\u003eApply to participate\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eMembers of the public will be able to participate in the project. The heat pumps and energy efficiency upgrades (where appropriate) in eligible homes will be provided free of charge in return for participating in the research and monitoring aspects of the project across the 3 selected areas of Great Britain mentioned above. Further details on how to express interest and take part will be available shortly from the delivery partners (E.On, OVO Energy and Warmworks).\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"contact\"\u003eContact\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor any query about participating in the project, please contact the delivery partners.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor any queries about the project, contact \u003ca href=\"mailto:heatpumpdemo@beis.gov.uk\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eheatpumpdemo@beis.gov.uk\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003c/div\u003e",
